text: Subiakto Tjakrawerdaya (10 August 1944 - 2 January 2021) was an Indonesian politician and businessman. He was born in the Cilacap Regency, Dutch East Indies. He was a member of the National Awakening Party. He was Minister of Cooperatives and Small Business from 1993 to 1998. Tjakrawedaya died on 2 January 2021 at a Jakarta hospital from COVID-19 at the age of 76. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Jakarta Category:Indonesian politicians Category:Indonesian businesspeople
